      <p class="fine-print">Summary</p>
      <p>We helped not-for-profit National Hemophilia Foundation (NHF) develop a social marketing approach to help college-aged women seek testing for von Willebrand disease (VWD), the most common inherited bleeding disorder. </p>
      <p>Social marketing applies traditional marketing to influence behavior for public benefit. In this case, NHF sought to increase the number of women seeking testing through social media campaigns and outreach to university health clinics.</p>
      <p>We helped NHF develop campaigns and write a persuasive grant proposal, resulting in a $2.3 million award from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).</p>
    </div>
